[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration as architectural primitive.** The assistant's value lives in the integration layer. The institutional integration team owns the per-system tool implementations, the cross-system reconciliation logic, the data-freshness tracking, and the graceful-degradation behavior when systems are unavailable. Skipping this and treating integrations as feature-by-feature work produces an assistant that knows about half of the patient's care.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordination-rules engine with clinical and care-management leadership ownership.** The coordination-gap detection rules are clinical and operational rules, owned by clinical leadership (per specialty for episode-specific rules) and care-management leadership (for cross-episode and operational rules), version-controlled, reviewed periodically, and stamped on every coordination-event record.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Action-versus-ask policy with explicit per-action rules.** The policy is institutionally specified, reviewed by compliance and legal counsel, and enforced both in the LLM's prompt and in the output-safety verification. Skipping this and letting the LLM decide when to take action versus ask permission produces an assistant that takes inappropriate actions at predictable rates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Records-transfer orchestration with cross-modality coverage.** The institution's records-transfer infrastructure (FHIR, Direct Trust, HIE, fax bridges, signed-release-form workflows) is integrated. The assistant tracks status across modalities and chooses the appropriate modality per transfer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-provider consent posture enforcement.** The patient's consent posture per provider, per purpose, per type of action is structured and enforced operationally. The compliance team reviews; the patient retains the right to revise.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous emergency screening across every utterance.** Same as the chronic-disease coach. The assistant routes acute emergencies immediately to the triage workflow or to direct emergency contacts; the assistant does not try to handle acute emergencies in-conversation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every status statement and every recommendation cites the source system or the institutional content it was based on, with version stamping. The citation is structured and the audit record preserves the citation trail.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-team and navigator integration as first-class capability.** Real-time alerts, weekly digests, monthly summaries, and warm-handoff infrastructure are part of production scope. The navigator-side tooling for taking over conversations, reviewing assistant-driven actions, and revising coordination rules is part of production scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Outcome tracking as core post-launch commitment.** The pipeline measures coordination-failure rates, time-to-treatment, dropped-referral rates, records-transfer success rates, duplicate-testing rates, no-show rates, transition-of-care quality, and patient-reported coordination burden, with per-cohort stratification.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, coordination-gap detection rate, gap-resolution rate, outcome metrics, citation-coverage rate, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, episode type, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, and digital-tool comfort level.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When integrated systems are unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully with patient-facing transparency about what data is unavailable. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble pulling the latest status from [system] right now; you can check directly via [alternate channel] or contact your navigator at [number]."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
